entities.name: Open Targets Tractability

columns.label: SM_B1_Approved Drug
columns.description: Bucket 1 (ChEMBL) Targets with approved (phase 4) SM drug

columns.label: SM_B2_Advanced Clinical
columns.description: Bucket 2 (ChEMBL) Targets with SM in clinical phase 2 or 3

columns.label: SM_B3_Phase 1 Clinical
columns.description: Bucket 3 (ChEMBL) Targets with SM in clinical phase 1

columns.label: SM_B4_Structure with Ligand
columns.description: Bucket 4 (PDB) Targets with crystal structures with ligands (excluding: buffer compounds, solvents, crystallization agents/additives and sugars)

columns.label: SM_B5_High-Quality Ligand
columns.description: Bucket 5 (ChEMBL) Targets with high quality ligands (PFI ≤7, structural_alerts ≤2, pchembl_value ≥5.5 or equivalent activity measure)

columns.label: SM_B6_High-Quality Pocket
columns.description: Bucket 6 (DrugEBIlity) Targets with score ≥0.7

columns.label: SM_B7_Med-Quality Pocket
columns.description: Bucket 7 (DrugEBIlity) Targets with 0 < score < 0.7

columns.label: SM_B8_Druggable Family
columns.description: Bucket 8 (Finan et al. 2017) Targets considered druggable using Finan et al's Druggable Genome

columns.label: SM Clinical precedence
columns.description: Assigned if any of the SM clinical buckets 1-3 are positive. (The category score is calculated by 1 * ['Bucket_1_sm'] + 0.7 * ['Bucket_2_sm'] + 0.2 * ['Bucket_3_sm'].)

columns.label: SM Discovery precedence
columns.description: Assigned if SM bucket 4 or 5 is the highest assigned bucket. (The category score is calculated by 0.7 * ['Bucket_4_sm'] + 0.3 * ['Bucket_5_sm'].)

columns.label: SM Predicted tractable
columns.description: Assigned if SM bucket 6, 7 or 8 is the highest assigned bucket. (The category score is calculated by 0.7 * ['Bucket_6_sm'] + 0.3 * ['Bucket_7_sm'] + 0.3 * ['Bucket_8_sm'].)

columns.label: AB_B1_Approved Drug
columns.description: Bucket 1 (ChEMBL) Targets with approved (phase 4) AB drug

columns.label: AB_B2_Advanced Clinical
columns.description: Bucket 2 (ChEMBL) Targets with AB in clinical phase 2 or 3

columns.label: AB_B3_Phase 1 Clinical
columns.description: Bucket 3 (ChEMBL) Targets with AB in clinical phase 1

columns.label: AB_B4_UniProt loc high conf
columns.description: Bucket 4 (UniProt loc) Targets with UniProt 'Subcellular location' terms indicative for plasma membrane, extracellular region/matrix, or secretion - high confidence

columns.label: AB_B5_GO CC high conf
columns.description: Bucket 5 (GO CC) Targets with GO 'Cellular component' terms indicative for plasma membrane, extracellular region/matrix, or secretion - high confidence [‘ECO:0000269’ or ‘ECO:0000305’]

columns.label: AB_B6_UniProt loc med conf
columns.description: Bucket 6 (UniProt loc) Targets with UniProt 'Subcellular location' terms indicative for plasma membrane, extracellular region/matrix, or secretion - medium confidence

columns.label: AB_B7_UniProt SigP or TMHMM
columns.description: Bucket 7 (UniProt SigP or TMHMM): Targets with predicted Signal Peptide or Trans-membrane regions, and not destined to organelles

columns.label: AB_B8_GO CC med conf
columns.description: Bucket 8 (GO CC) Targets with GO 'Cellular component' terms indicative for plasma membrane, extracellular region/matrix, or secretion - medium confidence

columns.label: AB_B9_Human Protein Atlas loc
columns.description: Bucket 9 (Human Protein Atlas) Targets with main location “Plasma membrane” - high confidence

columns.label: AB Clinical precedence
columns.description: Assigned if any of the AB clinical buckets 1-3 are positive. (The category score is calculated by 1 * ['Bucket_1_ab'] + 0.7 * ['Bucket_2_ab'] + 0.2 * ['Bucket_3_ab'].)

columns.label: AB Predicted Tractable High confidence
columns.description: Assigned if AB bucket 4 or 5 is the highest assigned bucket. (The category score is calculated by 0.7 * ['Bucket_4_ab'] + 0.3 * ['Bucket_5_ab'].)

columns.label: AB Predicted Tractable Medium to low confidence
columns.description: Assigned if AB bucket 6, 7, 8 or 9 is the highest assigned bucket. (The category score is calculated by 0.4 * ['Bucket_6_ab'] + 0.25 * ['Bucket_7_ab'] + 0.25 * ['Bucket_8_ab'] + 0.1 * ['Bucket_9_ab'].)

columns.label: PR_B1_Approved Drug
columns.description: Bucket 1 (-) Targets with approved (phase 4) PROTAC drug

columns.label: PR_B2_Advanced Clinical
columns.description: Bucket 2 (-) Targets with PROTAC in clinical phase 2 or 3

columns.label: PR_B3_Phase 1 Clinical
columns.description: Bucket 3 (-) Targets with PROTAC in clinical phase 1

columns.label: PR_B4_Literature
columns.description: Bucket 4 (Europe PMC) Targets mentioned in PROTAC literature (manually curated) + additional information via automated assessments

columns.label: PR_B5_UniProt Ubiquitination
columns.description: Bucket 5 (UniProt) Targets with UniProt keyword: "Ubl conjugation [KW-0832]"

columns.label: PR_B6_Database Ubiquitination
columns.description: Bucket 6 (PhosphoSitePlus, mUbiSiDa, Kim et al. 2011) Targets with reported ubiquitination sites in PhosphoSitePlus, mUbiSiDa (2013), or Kim et al. 2011

columns.label: PR_B7_Half-life Data
columns.description: Bucket 7 (Mathieson et al. 2018) Targets with available half-life data

columns.label: PR_B8_Small Molecule Binder
columns.description: Bucket 8 (ChEMBL) Targets with SM in ChEMBL with activity on target-based assay (pChEMBL ≥5)

columns.label: PROTAC Clinical_Precedence
columns.description: Assigned if any of the clinical buckets 1-3 are positive.

columns.label: PROTAC Literature_Precedence
columns.description: Assigned if literature bucket 4 is positive

columns.label: PROTAC Discovery_Opportunity
columns.description: Assigned for a given target if bucket (5 or 6) and bucket 7 and bucket 8 are assigned and the PROTAC_location_Bucket annotates high or medium confidence for "good" or "grey" location (location bucket score of 1, 2, 3 or 4).

columns.label: OC_B1_Approved Drug
columns.description: Bucket 1 (ChEMBL) Targets with approved (phase4) drug (other than SM or AB)

columns.label: OC_B2_Advanced Clinical
columns.description: Bucket 2 (ChEMBL) Targets with drug (other than SM or AB) in clinical phase 2 or 3

columns.label: OC_B3_Phase 1 Clinical
columns.description: Bucket 3 (ChEMBL) Targets with drug (other than SM or AB) in clinical phase 1

columns.label: OC Clinical_Precedence
columns.description: Assigned if any of the OtherCl clinical buckets 1-3 are positive.

columns.label: Level
columns.description: Tclin - These targets have activities in DrugCentral (ie. approved drugs) with known mechanism of action. Tchem - These targets have activities in ChEMBL, Guide to Pharmacology or DrugCentral that satisfy the activity thresholds. Tbio - These targets do not have known drug or small molecule activities that satisfy the activity thresholds AND satisfy one or more of the following criteria: 1. target is above the cutoff criteria for Tdark; 2. target is annotated with a Gene Ontology Molecular Function or Biological Process leaf term(s) with an Experimental Evidence code. Tdark - These are targets about which virtually nothing is known.
